  "texts": [
    "One way to illustrate this separation between the initial state and the ground state is to expand the initial state (for the sector K = π/2) into contributions from the ground state and excited states.",
    "We start defining the spectral weight in the ground state |Ψ gs ⟩ as P gs = | ⟨Ψ 0,F |Ψ gs ⟩ | 2, and the total spectral weight in the excited states asP ex = n>0 | ⟨Ψ 0,F |Ψ n ⟩ | 2.These weights satisfy the normalization condition: P gs + P ex = 1.",
    "To further characterize the initial state, we also evaluate the spectralweighted average of the local spin-spin operator, which reduces to:K cf (Ψ α) = n ⟨Ψ n |Ψ α ⟩ 2 ⟨Ψ α | Ŝf • Ŝc |Ψ n ⟩ ⇒ K cf (Ψ gs) = ⟨Ψ gs | Ŝf • Ŝc |Ψ gs ⟩.",
    "(A1)Figure 14 shows the spectral weight distribution of the initial state.",
    "For a strong Kondo coupling, the initial state has an equal contribution from the ground state and excited states."
